HEADWORD: Calendulin
<hw>Ca*len"du*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A gummy or mucilaginous tasteless substance obtained from the
marigold or calendula, and analogous to bassorin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

